Titolo: World Games (video game)

Anno: 1986

Descrizione: World Games is a sports video game developed by Epyx for the Commodore 64 in 1986. Versions for the Apple IIGS, Amstrad CPC, ZX Spectrum, Sega Master System and other contemporary systems were also released. The NES version was released by Milton Bradley, and ported by Software Creations on behalf of producer Rare. A Virtual Console version was released in Europe on April 25, 2008.
The game was a continuation in the Epyx sports line that previously released extremely successful titles such as Summer Games and Winter Games.